Wale Oyewale The Oyo State governor, Seyi Makinde, on Friday, paid a condolence visit to the former Vice-Chancellor of the University of Ibadan, Prof. A.B.O.O Oyediran, on the passage of his wife, Revd. Tola Oyediran. The governor’s mother, Chief Abigail Makinde, passed on 24 hours before Oyediran’s death. The governor consoled the family over the death of Mama Oyediran, the first daughter of late Chief Obafemi Awolowo. Until her death, she was the chairman of the African Newspapers of Nigeria Plc., publishers of the Tribune titles. Copyright PUNCH.
